LUMPY SKIN DISEASE - BURUNDI: (KIRUNDO) BOVINE, OIE
***************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 1 Aug 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2016; 29(31) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=20621


Lumpy skin disease, Burundi
----------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 1 Aug 2016 from Dr Deogratias Nsanganiyumwami, [Director Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture and Livestock], Gitega, Burundi

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 25 Jul 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 29 Jul 2016
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 30 Nov 2015
Causal agent: Lumpy skin disease [LSD] virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Outbreak 1: Commune Busoni, Kirundo
Date of start of the outbreak: 25 Jul 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 3385 / 20 / - / 0 / 0
Affected population: Affected animals consist of cattle of all ages and both sexes with, according to information collected from farmers, sudden deaths in calves and abortions; the number of dead animals and of abortions are unknown.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 0.59 / ** / ** / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Samples taken were skin biopsies and sera. Biopsies were tested by conventional PCR. The DNA extracted and tested positive was kept for sequencing. Among the 10 tested biopsies, 3 were positive, and DNA was kept for, if possible, virus sequencing. This is the 1st laboratory confirmation of lumpy skin disease in Burundi.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Veterinary Laboratory in Bujumbura (National laboratory) / Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 29 Jul 2016 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[During the past few years, Burundi has submitted its 6-monthly and annual reports only for the year 2015. No information is available for the years 2013 and 2014.

According to information submitted in their annual report 2015, LSD was reported as "present" in the country. 13 outbreaks were reported during this year. These were located in the provinces of Cibitoke, Kirundo (where the current outbreak is located), Ruyigi, Kayanza, Makamba and Muyinga. See report at http://tinyurl.com/j2wacmz.

Maps of Burundi can be seen at http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/burundi_map.htm. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4388639,172.]
